[[File:Shayzien soldiers.png|thumb|300px|Soldiers of the Shayzien Army performing training exercises in the [[Shayzien Encampment]].]]
The '''Shayzien Army''' is the military force of the city of [[Shayzien]]. It consists of six regiments, with [[Lord Shiro Shayzien]], the leader of the Shayzien House, being the commander-in-chief of the Shayzien Army.{{CiteNPC|npc=Lord Shiro Shayzien|quote=I am the ruler of Shayzien and the commander-in-chief of the Shayzien Army.}} Though other cities, excluding [[Arceuus]], have some form of militia, the Shayzien Army is the largest military force in [[Great Kourend]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Captain Bruce|quote=While the Shayzien Army is by far the largest military force in Kourend, the other cities still have some form of militia, apart from Arceuus of course.}}

Despite the size of the Shayzien Army and their importance to the defence of Great Kourend, there are two areas in particular in which they are lacking: defence against magical arts and a naval force.{{CiteNPC|npc=Sergeant Ricardo|quote=I suppose we don't really have any magical capabilities. That's more an Arceuus thing.|name=magic}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Sergeant Ricardo|quote=We don't have a navy, so can't really deal with any threats at sea.}} The naval force is meant to be lead by the [[Piscarilius House]], but the current head, [[Lady Shauna Piscarilius]], has no interest in forming the Kourend Navy.{{CiteNPC|npc=Sergeant Ricardo|quote=Lady Piscarilius is meant to be in charge of the Kourend Navy. Problem is, it doesn't actually exist. [She]  has little interest in that sort of thing.}} Despite this, there is pushback from the rest of the kingdom for Lord Shayzien to form a Shayzien Navy due to concerns over Shayzien having too much military power.{{CiteNPC|npc=Sergeant Ricardo|quote=Lord Shayzien wants to establish a Shayzien Navy instead, but there's a lot of pushback from the rest of the kingdom. They worry about Shayzien having too much power.}}

==History==
The Shayzien Army was not always the large military force that is now. During the reign of King Hosidius V, [[Armed Forces Report|a report]] was written by Lord Rickard Shayzien that outlined the strength of the Shayzien Army. The army contained only 104 personnel, 12 of which were officers and 4 of which were medical staff.{{CiteText|text=Armed Forces Report|page=2, 4|quote=Officers: XII ... Medical Roster: IV ... Total Personnel: CIV}}

Lord Rickard Shayzien identified three main areas that needed improvement: the size of the army,{{CiteText|text=Armed Forces Report|page=5|quote=We must expand our forces substantially in order to face these threats and defend the Kingdom of Great Kourend.}} officer training,{{CiteText|text=Armed Forces Report|page=6|quote=We must invest in officer class training in order to maintain obedience throughout the ranks.}} and the army's ability to defend against magical attacks.{{CiteText|text=Armed Forces Report|page=6|quote=Furthermore, we live in a time were magical discoveries are made every day, and the threat of a magical based attack increases with each discovery. Standard forces are not prepared to battle such a threat. We must invest in defence against these dark arts.}}

In order to accomplish these goals, Lord Rickard Shayzien recommended an overhaul of the Shayzien Army's structure. He suggested that the army create three regiments: The Elder Warriors, Twisted Archers, and Kodai Mages.{{CiteText|text=Armed Forces Report|page=8|quote=The armed forces shall separate into three regiments: - Elder Warriors - Twisted Archers - Kodai Mages}} Each regiment would consist of 200 soldiers and be lead by a general who reported to Lord Rickard Shayzien directly.{{CiteText|text=Armed Forces Report|page=8|quote=Each regiment will consist of two hundred personnel under the command of a General, with each General reporting to myself.}}

Whether or not any of these recommendations were taken up is unknown. Since the writing of this report, the size of the army has greatly increased. However, none of the three recommended regiments currently exist,{{CiteNPC|npc=Commissioner Anwar|quote=[What are the six regiments?] The Intelligence Corps, the Medical Corps, the Engineering Corps, the Logistics Corps, the Rangers and of course, the Infantry.|name=regiments}} and the Shayzien Army has no magical capabilities.{{NamedRef|magic}} Despite this, there is some evidence that these regiments were created at one point in the past. A sergeant in the 38th decade, Yan Mattin, was court-martialed for refusing to capture civilians and bring them to [[Xeric]].{{CiteText|text=Chronicles of Xeric|page=14-15|quote=Sgt Mattin refused to follow orders pertaining to the acquisition and delivery of civilians to the chambers of His Lordship, Xeric, on the day of 3,470 - 37}} He was sentenced to be executed by a twisted archer,{{CiteText|text=Chronicles of Xeric|page=15|quote=Sgt Mattin pleads guilty to the charge of Gross Insubordination for which the sentence is execution by twisted archer.}} which is perhaps a reference to the aforementioned Twisted Archers regiment.

==Enlisting==
[[File:Shayzien Administration.png|thumb|250px|The Shayzien Administration, where Shayzien is run from. The recruitment office is also found here.]]
Most personnel in the Shayzien Army are comprised of [[Shayzien]] citizens, though in recent years more people from the other cities enlist in Shayzien.{{CiteNPC|npc=Captain Bruce|quote=Every year we see more people from outside Shayzien enlist.}} For example, [[Lydia Fullore]], who is from [[Hosidius]], enlisted in the Shayzien Army before joining the [[Royal Guard]].

Those who wish to enlist in the Shayzien Army typically make their way to the recruitment office in the [[Shayzien Administration]], though enlistees must be a resident of Great Kourend.{{CiteNPC|npc=Captain Bruce|quote=It's in the rules I'm afraid. Only citizens of Kourend are allowed to join the Shayzien Army.}} In the past, only Shayzien citizens could enlist in the army, but this was expanded to all citizens of Great Kourend during the reign of [[King Byrne I]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Captain Bruce|quote=Well at one time only citizens of Shayzien could join the army. It wasn't until the reign of King Byrne I that people from other parts of the kingdom were allowed to enlist.}} Despite this, prospective enlistees from other cities are more likely to join their local city force.{{CiteNPC|npc=Captain Bruce|quote=Even if someone from elsewhere in the kingdom wants to become a soldier, they're far more likely to join their local city force than come to us.}}

==Regiments==
The Shayzien Army consists of six regiments: The Intelligence Corps, the Medical Corps, the Engineering Corps, the Logistics Corps, the Rangers, and the Infantry.{{NamedRef|regiments}} Though not a regiment of the army itself, the Shayzien Constabulary, who mainly deal with internal threats to the kingdom, is considered a part of Shayzien Army.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commissioner Anwar|quote=The Shayzien Army is split into six regiments plus the Shayzien Constabulary. While the six regiments are jointly responsible for protecting Kourend from external threats, we deal with issues closer to home.}}

Each regiment is led by a general who reports to [[Lord Shayzien]], while the Constabulary is led by a commissioner.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commissioner Anwar|quote=Each regiment is led by a general who reports directly to Lord Shayzien.}}
[[File:Infirmary.png|thumb|250px|The nurses of the Medical Corps take care of [[wounded soldier]]s in the [[Shayzien Encampment]].]]
The current known leaders of the seven major divisions are:
* Intelligence Corps - [[General Salara]] ([[Captain Ginea]] leads the investigation unit of the division){{CiteNPC|npc=Captain Ginea|quote=I'm in charge of the investigations unit.}}
* Medical Corps - Not known
* Engineering Corps - [[General Kilian]]
* Logistics Corps - [[General Babacus]]
* Rangers - Not known
* Infantry - [[General Vir]]
* Constabulary - [[Commissioner Anwar]]

Despite their appearance, the Kourend [[Royal Guard]] are a separate entity from the Shayzien Army; instead, they directly serve the ruler of Great Kourend,{{CiteNPC|npc=Commander Fullore|quote=Unlike the Shayzien Army, the Royal Guard serve the ruler of the kingdom directly.}} and are currently lead by Commander [[Lydia Fullore]], who ensures that they are well trained and supplied.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commander Fullore|quote=The Kourend Royal Guard protect and serve the ruler of Kourend. As their leader, I am responsible for ensuring that the Royal Guard are well trained and well supplied.}}

==Equipment==
All Shayzien Army soldiers wear a special type of armour known as [[Shayzien armour]]. There are five different tiers of Shayzien armour, with each tier offering greater protection against the green acidic attacks of [[lizardman shaman]]s. 

The tier of armour a given soldier wears reflects their skill and rank in the Shayzien Army:
*[[Shayzien armour (tier 1)|Tier one]] - Soldiers in basic training.{{CiteNPC|npc=Armourer (tier 1)|quote=My job is to coordinate tier 1 equipment. That's the basic training kit, so it's nothing fancy.}}
*[[Shayzien armour (tier 2)|Tier two]] - Soldiers who have passed basic training but are not combat ready.{{CiteNPC|npc=Armourer (tier 2)|quote=My job is to coordinate tier 2 equipment. That's what they wear when they've passed basic training but aren't ready for real combat.}}
*[[Shayzien armour (tier 3)|Tier three]] - Combat ready, but not elite soldiers.{{CiteNPC|npc=Armourer (tier 3)|quote=My job is to coordinate tier 3 equipment, for warriors who can't handle the fancy equipment we make for their elite fighters.}}
*[[Shayzien armour (tier 4)|Tier four]] - Soldiers in the upper ranks of the army.{{CiteNPC|npc=Armourer (tier 4)|quote=My job is to coordinate tier 4 equipment. It's pretty good stuff, used by their upper ranks.}}
*[[Shayzien armour (tier 5)|Tier five]] - Chief officers and elite soldiers.{{CiteNPC|npc=Armourer (tier 5)|quote=My job is to coordinate tier 5 equipment. That's the best stuff, for their chief officers and elite fighters.}}

==Current functions==
The aim of the six regiments of the Shayzien Army is to protect the Kingdom of Great Kourend from external threats, while the Constabulary seeks to protect the kingdom from internal threats. However, these roles are often merged together.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commissioner Anwar|quote=On paper [the Constabulary is] totally separate from the regiments. However, in reality you are correct. The distinction between internal and external threats grows murkier by the day.}}

===Lizardmen===
[[File:Battlefront.png|thumb|250px|The Shayzien Infantry battle the lizardmen in the Battlefront.]]
One of the main aims of the Shayzien Army is the containment of [[lizardmen]] in the [[Lizardman Canyon]], as well as guarding the western border of the Kingdom. As a result, a large number of troops are deployed in [[Shayziens' Wall]] and the [[Kebos]] [[Battlefront]] to defend the Kingdom against the lizardmen.{{CiteNPC|npc=Lord Shiro Shayzien|quote=What I can tell you is that our main focus right now is the Lizardman threat. We've moved a great number of troops into the Kebos Lowlands to combat the issue.}}

The army has seen success in their efforts to contain the lizardmen, having made many areas of the [[Kebos Lowlands]] that were threatened by the lizardmen safe for civilians again.{{CiteNPC|npc=Lord Shiro Shayzien|quote=Absolutely, we've pushed the Lizardmen back to the point where we're finally able to allow citizens such as yourself into the region.}} For example, the fertile land south of [[Mount Karuulm]] was cleared out to build the [[Farming Guild]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Guildmaster Jane|quote=After the Shayzien Army cleared out the lizardmen in this area, I founded this guild with some fellow Hosidius farmers.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Gordon|quote=Lord Hosidius made a deal with Lord Shayzien and the lizardmen were cleared out to make room for the Farming Guild.}}

A current concern of the Shayzien Army is the ability of the lizardmen to cut off the army's connection to Lovakengj. Should a blockade occur, the Shayzien supply lines would be severely impacted. As leader of the Logistics Corps, General Babacus has been tasked with creating contingency plans should the army's supply lines be cut.{{CiteNPC|npc=General Babacus|quote=If they ever succeed in cutting us off from Lovakengj, our supply lines will be severely constrained, and I must work on alternate plans}} The connection between Lovakengj and Shayzien is especially important because the Shayzien Army sources most of its from Shayzien. {{CiteNPC|npc=Armourer (tier 5)|quote=The Shayzien armies always want supplies of armour, and the artisans of Lovakengj are responsible for supplying it.}}

===Organized crime===
{{Main|Tackle organised crime}}
The Shayzien Army, specifically the Constabulary in conjunction with help from the Intelligence Corps, has been tasked with rooting out criminal gangs in [[Port Piscarilius]]. That the Constabulary is receiving support from the Intelligence Corps is an example of how the distinctions between the different regiments are the Constabulary have blurred in the army over time.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commissioner Anwar|quote=More and more we find ourselves working alongside the Intelligence Corps and the other regiments. In particular, they've been supporting us in combating the rising gang threat in Port Piscarilius.}}

===Governance of Shayzien===
Another task of the Shayzien Army is the actual running of the city of Shayzien itself.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commissioner Anwar|quote=Indeed. There's more of a separation between the city of Shayzien and the Shayzien Army now than there used to be, but this will likely always be a military settlement.}} The day to day operations of running Shayzien take place in the Shayzien Administration building.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commissioner Anwar|quote=This is the Shayzien Administration. The city of Shayzien is run from here.}} With most of the leaders of the Shayzien Army in the [[Shayzien Encampment]] fighting off the lizardman threat, Commissioner Anwar has been left in charge.{{CiteNPC|npc=Commissioner Anwar|quote=A lot of focus right now is on the war with the lizardmen. Most senior members of the Shayzien Army, including Lord Shayzien himself, are working out of the Shayzien Encampment instead.}}

The Shayzien Army also operates the [[Shayzien Prison]], which is located to the west of Shayzien city. In addition to local criminals, the Shayzien prison is also tasked with holding the arrested members of the [[Kourend Council]] after the events of [[A Kingdom Divided]].

